countries in the world.

11
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:05,880
Yet Singapore is also one of the most
densely populated countries with over 5 million people living on the main island.

12
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:11,300
Singapore consists of one main island and
over 60 smaller islands.

13
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:16,660
The main island is linked by bridges to
peninsula Malaysia in the north.

14
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:21,160
To the south lies Indonesia and the Riau
Islands.

15
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:28,320
With limited land, Singapore has had to
maximize land usage through careful urban planning.

16
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:32,960
Singapore has little variation in terrain
due to its small size.

17
00:01:33,460 --> 00:01:37,160
The terrain consists mostly of sedimentary
rock and granite.

18
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:40,060
The main island has a number of low hills,

19
00:01:40,580 --> 00:01:43,740
including Bukit Timah, one of the highest
points.

20
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:50,980
Singapore's coastline has dramatically
changed over the years through extensive land reclamation projects.

21
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:56,400
Several rivers flow from the center of the
island towards the coastlines.

22
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,680
Due to rapid development,

23
