77
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:46,500
Singapore has long served as an important
port and commercial centre in Southeast Asia.

78
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:52,580
The earliest known settlements in
Singapore date back to the 2nd century CE.

79
00:05:53,120 --> 00:06:03,260
The island was located on trade routes
between India and China and was referred to as Temasek, meaning sea town in Javanese.

80
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:06,980
From the 14th to early 19th century,

81
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:12,640
Singapore was part of the Malaka Sultanate
and then the Johor Sultanate.

82
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:17,800
During this time, a small fishing village
emerged at the mouth of the Singapore River.

83
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,160
In 1819,

84
00:06:19,940 --> 00:06:25,540
British statesmen Sir Thomas Stamford
Raffles established a British port on the island.

85
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:29,880
The port formally became a British colony
in 1824.

86
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:36,420
Under British rules, Singapore grew into a
major hub for regional and international trade.

87
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:41,660
Immigrants from China, India and the Malay
Archipelago flocked to Singapore.

88
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:47,260
Its population and economic importance
expanded enormously during the colonial era.

89
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:50,120
From 1942 to 1945,

90
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:53,660
Japan occupied Singapore during World War
II.

91
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:57,660
The British surrender marked their largest
military defeat.

92
00:06:58,220 --> 00:07:01,840
During the occupation, Singapore was
renamed Sionan.

93
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:06,000
The Japanese occupation ended after the
war in 1945.

94
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:14,340
Singapore then briefly became part of the
British military administration before returning to colonial rule.

95
00:07:14,980 --> 00:07:16,060
After the war,

96
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,880
Singapore progressively moved towards self
-governance.

97
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:27,940
The People's Action Party won the first
general election under full internal self -government in 1959.

98
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,920
On August 9, 1965,

99
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:38,780
Singapore declared independence from
Britain and merged with Malaya, Sabah and Sarawak to form Malaysia.

